dslRule:
new java.util.HashSet<$E$>()
=> new java.util.HashSet<>()
;;

new java.util.HashSet<$E$>($args$)
=> new java.util.HashSet<>($args$)
;;

new java.util.ArrayList<$E$>()
=> new java.util.ArrayList<>()
;;

new java.util.ArrayList<$E$>($args$)
=> new java.util.ArrayList<>($args$)
;;

new java.util.Hashtable<$K, $V$>()
=> new java.util.Hashtable<>()
;;

new java.util.Hashtable<$K, $V$>($args$)
=> new java.util.Hashtable<>($args$)
;;

/*!id: jdt.internal.generateconstructor.selectiondialog.add-allowempty-flag*/
/*!description: Modifies the internal GenerateConstructorUsingFieldsSelectionDialog constructor call to its superclass SourceActionDialog, adding a 'true' argument to allow empty field lists. This enables generating constructors even when a class has no fields.*/
/*!severity: info*/
super($parent, $labelProvider, $contentProvider, $editor, $type, $isConstructor)
:: inClass("org.eclipse.jdt.internal.ui.actions.GenerateConstructorUsingFieldsSelectionDialog")
=> super($parent, $labelProvider, $contentProvider, $editor, $type, $isConstructor, true)
;;

dslRuleAfterChange:
A hypothetical DSL extension for this might look like:

METHOD_DECLARATION:
void $name($params$) {
  $body$
}
=>
IF_NOT_NULL_PREPEND:
if ($field == null) {
  return null;
}
;;

But this syntax for injecting new control flow is not currently part of the DSL.

